    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "## Summary\n\nNeovim contains a double-free vulnerability (CVE-2024-41965) inherited from Vim in `dialog_changed()`. When abandoning a buffer, `b_sfname` and `b_ffname` can point to the same allocation (set by `fname_expand()`), but are freed independently via `XFREE_CLEAR()`, causing a double-free.\n\n## Vulnerability Details\n\n- **CVE**: [CVE-2024-41965](https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2024-41965)\n- **Type**: Double-Free (CWE-415)\n- **Affected File**: `src/nvim/ex_cmds2.c`, lines 227-231\n- **Root Cause**: `fname_expand()` at line 3578-3579 sets `*sfname = *ffname` when sfname is NULL. Later, `dialog_changed()` frees both independently.\n\n## Vulnerable Code\n\n```c\n// src/nvim/ex_cmds2.c:227-231\nif (empty_bufname) {\n    buf->b_fname = NULL;\n    XFREE_CLEAR(buf->b_ffname);   // frees the allocation\n    XFREE_CLEAR(buf->b_sfname);   // DOUBLE-FREE if sfname == ffname!\n    unchanged(buf, true, false);\n}\n```\n\n## Recommended Fix\n\nApply the Vim fix (patch 9.1.0648, [vim/vim@b29f4abc](https://github.com/vim/vim/commit/b29f4abcd4b3)):\n\nAdd a guard before freeing `b_sfname`:\n```c\nif (buf->b_sfname != buf->b_ffname)\n    XFREE_CLEAR(buf->b_sfname);\nelse\n    buf->b_sfname = NULL;\nXFREE_CLEAR(buf->b_ffname);\n```\n\n## References\n\n- Vim fix: https://github.com/vim/vim/commit/b29f4abcd4b3\n- CVE: https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2024-41965\n- Verified on Neovim v0.13.0-dev (latest master, commit 9c5fba5)",
