            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Thank you @zeertzjq for the detailed analysis.\n\nYou are correct — I missed the fact that `fix_fname()` returns either a newly-allocated string or NULL, which means after `fname_expand()`, `*sfname` and `*ffname` will always point to different allocations (or one will be NULL). The double-free condition that exists in Vim's code path cannot occur in Neovim's version.\n\nI apologize for the incorrect report. My static analysis traced the `XFREE_CLEAR(b_sfname)` / `XFREE_CLEAR(b_ffname)` pattern but did not properly follow the `fix_fname()` return value semantics.\n\nThank you for taking the time to review this.",
